(1123, 9, '2021-02-16 19:21:07', '2021-02-16 19:21:07', '<span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>RNC Client Onboarding Coordinator, Full Time, Toronto</strong></span>\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Client Onboarding Administrator to provide support to the Residential New Construction department in the Simply Group of Companies. You will be a part of a team of professionals working to provide an exceptional customer experience for our Builder Partners and Homeowners.\r\n\r\nThe Simply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy efficient residential and commercial solutions so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of over 400 employees take an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into four categories; Home Comfort, Lighting, New Construction and Lending. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"http://local-mysimplygreen/\">http://local-mysimplygreen/</a>\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate will be organized &amp; motivated, with the ability to think outside the box to improve the onboarding journey for our Clients.\r\n\r\nThe Client Onboarding Administrator is also responsible for ensuring all new Homeowners are successfully registered for billing and our homeowner database is kept up to date.\r\n\r\nWe are a high-growth company and have been recognized as one of Canadas Best Places to Work. Our team values a make-it-happen mindset and looks to bring on leaders who are looking to grow in a fast-paced environment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Act as the primary point of contact to onboard our Builder Partners, ensuring they are knowledgeable of and adhere to the RNC process</li>\r\n 	<li>Establish strong relationships with Builder Partners to receive and ensure accuracy of closing information within required timeframes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintain database of homeowner closing information with accurate status updates for each delivered unit of equipment (e.g, closed, not billing, etc,)</li>\r\n 	<li>Communicate with homeowners to ensure they are successfully registered for billing</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure billing platform is updated with new homeowner data</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure Welcome Packages are sent to all new homeowners</li>\r\n 	<li>Initiate billing for all RNC customers who have moved into new construction homes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide KPI and ad hoc reporting to management as required</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate across departments to investigate and solve billing discrepancies and errors</li>\r\n 	<li>Support process improvement initiatives and new process roll outs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Key Competencies:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Experience in delivering client-focused solutions based on customer needs.</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent verbal and written communications skills.</li>\r\n 	<li>Self-motivated and able to thrive in a results-driven environment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Natural relationship builder with integrity, reliability, and maturity.</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical abilities to develop strategies and implement ideas aimed at improving the onboarding experience for Clients</li>\r\n 	<li>Make-it-happen mentality</li>\r\n 	<li>Honesty and integrity</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong timeline management, with the ability to prioritize competing tasks.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to process high volumes of work with accuracyand attention to detail</li>\r\n 	<li>Intermediate knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (PowerPoint, Outlook &amp; Word)</li>\r\n 	<li>Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Excel preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process. </strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>', 'RNC Client Onboarding Coordinator', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rnc-client-onboarding-coordinator__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-04 18:23:11', '2021-03-04 18:23:11', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1123', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1124, 9, '2021-02-16 19:22:41', '2021-02-16 19:22:41', '<strong>Vendor Sales Manager</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Full Time, Toronto (Temporarily Remote)</em>\r\n\r\nThe Green Living Show has successfully pivoted to the Green Living Store, creating a curated online marketplace offering sustainable products from eco focused and responsible businesses who support the change we want to see in our world. Check us out at <a href=\"https://greenlivingstore.ca/\">https://greenlivingstore.ca/</a>\r\n\r\nOur team is looking for a Vendor Sales Manager who is passionate about the environment and showcasing top-quality green products while providing a top-quality vendor experience. This role will be responsible to search out vendors to curate a robust, eco-focused product suite that drives sales, environmental awareness and preservation. The Green Living Store offers a zero-cost entry threshold for our vendors and the Vendors Sales Manager will create an exceptional vendor experience from prospecting, through onboarding, to day to day vendor relationship management. The store will rely on the Vendor Sales Managers expertise on the trends in the green space to ensure we are offering a relevant and responsible consumer experience and connecting our vendors to eco-focused customers. This role is pivotal to the Green Living Stores success and is a key member of the GLS team.\r\n\r\n<strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Prospect and procure new vendors to the Green Living Store, in line with company targets and objectives.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a positive and seamless vendor onboarding experience to the Green Living Store</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage vendor relationships to ensure mutual success and close the feedback loop to find vendor experience and process improvements.</li>\r\n 	<li>Leverage strong relationship building to reach out to our current vendor roster for sales promotions, campaign features and other initiatives to drive revenue.</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with the marketing team on campaigns, weekly e-blasts, and ensuring that vendor promos are executed seamlessly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Partner with business operations to ensure seamless flow through from vendor onboarding to day to day sales activity, act as bridge between customers and vendors to ensure 5-star shopping experience.</li>\r\n 	<li>Keep on top of trends in the Green/Eco-focused space to support marketing campaigns, consumer communications, and target appropriate vendors and suppliers.</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage part-time staff to ensure effective prospecting pipeline generation and achievement of prospecting targets.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ad hoc projects, as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>2+ years of B2B sales experience.</li>\r\n 	<li>2+ years of experience in vendor relationship management.</li>\r\n 	<li>1-3 years of experience in e-commerce/online retail.</li>\r\n 	<li>Thorough knowledge of the green space, environmental community, sustainable practices.</li>\r\n 	<li>Professional experience in online product merchandising an asset.</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in online green content creation an asset.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Simply Group offers a competitive salary, performance bonus opportunities and participation in our group benefits program. All candidates will be considered; however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply is happy to provide accommodation through the recruitment and interview process, and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Vendor Sales Manager - Green Living Show', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vendor-sales-manager-green-living-show__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-04 18:23:11', '2021-03-04 18:23:11', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1124', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
