,\"year\":\"2020\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cimg class=\\u0022alignnone  wp-image-251\\u0022 src=\\u0022http://local-mysimplygreen/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/logo-simply-retail-300x139.png\\u0022 alt=\\u0022\\u0022 width=\\u0022164\\u0022 height=\\u002276\\u0022 /\\u003e \\u003cimg class=\\u0022alignnone  wp-image-245\\u0022 src=\\u0022http://local-mysimplygreen/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/logo-home-depot-300x300.png\\u0022 alt=\\u0022\\u0022 width=\\u002272\\u0022 height=\\u002272\\u0022 /\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eLaunched Simply Green Retail Services with Home Depot.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eNamed Best Business of the Year (+100 employees) by the CanadianSME National Business Awards.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eWere proud to have been ranked as Great Place To Work, 5 years in a row.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cimg class=\\u0022alignnone size-medium wp-image-1011\\u0022 src=\\u0022http://local-mysimplygreen/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/logo-CanadianSME-Award-300x125.png\\u0022 alt=\\u0022Simply Green has been named Best Business of the Year (+100 employees)\\u0022 width=\\u0022300\\u0022 height=\\u0022125\\u0022 /\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cimg class=\\u0022alignnone  wp-image-1027\\u0022 src=\\u0022http://local-mysimplygreen/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/logo-GPTW-297x300.png\\u0022 alt=\\u0022Great Place to Work\\u0022 width=\\u0022147\\u0022 height=\\u0022148\\u0022 /\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Green has been named Best Business of the Year (+100 employees)\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eThis honour was announced at an event hosted by CanadianSME Business Magazine in partnership with Cisco, Lenovo, and RBC, and is recognition of Simply Greens rapid assent to the ranks of Canadas most successful and leading companies.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1011,\"no-dot\":\"no-dot\",\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: 400px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-style\":\"button\",\"link-url\":\"/press-release/simply-green-has-been-named-best-business-of-the-year-100-employees/\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Green recognized as one of the Best Workplaces in Canada\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eOur employees have always been our biggest asset, so providing them with a positive, inclusive, fun and rewarding work environment is a priority for us. Each year, we strive to build a company culture that empowers and inspires performance. Our goal is to deliver the best possible employee experience, and, to make that happen, we are continuously looking for ways to raise the bar, said Lawrence Krimker, CEO of Simply Group.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1027,\"no-dot\":\"no-dot\",\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: 250px;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-url\":\"http://local-mysimplygreen/press_release/simply-green-recognized-as-one-of-the-best-workplaces-in-canada/\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Group Completes Acquisition of Dealnet in Transaction Valued at over $243 Million\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003e\\u0022The Dealnet acquisition is highly strategic, and complementary to our business. With Dealnet on board we have further cemented our competitive advantage in the home improvement financing space. Our unprecedented dealer network will have access to a best-in-class suite of financing products and a significantly improved digital application experience,\\u0022 said\\u003cspan class=\\u0022xn-person\\u0022\\u003eLawrence Krimker\\u003c/span\\u003e, Founder and CEO of Simply Group. \\u0022No other Canadian home financing company can offer comparable opportunities to its dealers. We will continually look for new ways to enhance our dealer programs and bolster the value we offer them.\\u0022\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":847,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/simply-group-completes-acquisition-of-dealnet-in-transaction-valued-at-over-243-million-808176167.html\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Group Acquisition Corp. Acquires 93.13% of Dealnet Capital Corp. and Commences Compulsory Acquisition\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eWith the acquisition of Dealnet well on its way towards successful completion, I would like to thank Dealnets valued shareholders, employees and partners for their overwhelming support, said Brent Houlden, Dealnet Chief Executive Officer. Were delighted that our strategic review process resulted in a premium offer for shareholders and believe that we have found an ideal owner for the business in Simply Group and industry veteran Lawrence Krimker.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1064,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/simply-group-completes-acquisition-of-dealnet-in-transaction-valued-at-over-243-million-808176167.html\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Dealnet and Simply Group Acquisition Corp. Announce Successful Take-up of Shares under the Offer\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eWe would like to thank all of the Dealnet shareholders who have already taken advantage of this opportunity to realize the immediate value and tendered their shares. We are pleased to have taken up over 74% of Dealnets shares, said Lawrence Krimker, CEO of The Simply Group.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1058,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2020/10/15/2109099/0/en/Dealnet-and-Simply-Group-Acquisition-Corp-Announce-Successful-Take-up-of-Shares-under-the-Offer.html\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Group Completes Acquisition of Snap Financial Group in a Transaction Valued at $511 Million\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003e\\u0022SNAP Financial Group\'s strong portfolio and extensive dealer network unlocks immediate scale-efficiency and value for Simply Group, providing us with a distinct market advantage that we will leverage to deliver extraordinary growth in both assets under management and shareholder value,\\u0022 said\\u003cspan class=\\u0022xn-person\\u0022\\u003eLawrence Krimker\\u003c/span\\u003e, Founder and CEO of Simply Group. \\u0022The combined strengths of Simply Group and SNAP will enable us to continue to drive innovation across a much-broader customer base with industry-changing products and services.\\u0022\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1066,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-style\":\"button\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/simply-group-completes-acquisition-of-snap-financial-group-in-a-transaction-valued-at-511-million-885985213.html\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Group Completes $71 Million Acquisition of Home Capital Groups Point-of-Sale Retail Lending Portfolio\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eThe sale is aligned with Home Capitals strategy to exit non-core activities, while Simply Group looks to further fuel its growth in the consumer finance business by diversifying its product and consumer lending offerings beyond home energy solutions to home improvement generally.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1057,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200903005822/en/\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"VersaBank Adds Simply Group Financial as Point-of-Sale Partner With Initial Financing of $72 Million\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003eWe are thrilled to welcome Simply Group Financial as a new Point-of-Sale Financing partner, said David Taylor, President and CEO, VersaBank. Its a great time to be joining forces with Simply Group Financial with the home improvement industry experiencing a boom as Canadians spend more of their discretionary income on home renovations and upgrades amidst the pandemic. VersaBanks Point-of-Sale Financing business has been the primary driver of the significant expansion of our lending portfolio for the last eight years and we see this partnership as a tremendous opportunity for both organizations to execute on their growth strategies.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1065,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-style\":\"button\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200908005292/en/VersaBank-Adds-Simply-Group-Financial-Point-of-Sale-Partner\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Green Home Services To Make Friendly, Premium All-Cash Offer to Acquire Dealnet\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003e\\u0022Simply Green has invested strategically to become a leader in the home comfort and home energy solutions sector, and this deal represents the next step in our continued growth. We are pleased this transaction will be adding over $200 million of finance receivables to our growing business, said Lawrence Krimker, Chief Executive Officer of Simply Group. With Simply Greens expansive and growing product offerings, and Dealnets underlying strength, we believe this acquisition will benefit our customers and investors and positions us well for the future. We look forward to commencing the tender process as soon as possible.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1051,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2020/10/27/2114761/0/en/Simply-Group-Acquisition-Corp-Acquires-93-13-of-Dealnet-Capital-Corp-and-Commences-Compulsory-Acquisition.html\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Investors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '156-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-02-16 19:28:31', '2021-02-16 19:28:31', '', 156, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/156-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1127, 9, '2021-02-17 16:51:48', '2021-02-17 16:51:48', '<strong><u>Dispatch Coordinator  Installation Department, Full Time, Toronto.</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Find your spot at Simply Group!</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Simply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy efficient residential and commercial solutions so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of over 400 employees take an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into four categories; Home Comfort, Lighting, New Construction and Lending. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"http://local-mysimplygreen/\">http://local-mysimplygreen/</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Position Summary</u></strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Green Home Services Installation team is looking for a Dispatch Coordinator. You will be apart of a team of professionals working to ensure all our clients and technicians feel like family.\r\n\r\nThe Dispatch Coordinator will be responsible for scheduling installation appointments and/or service requests. The day to day duties of the role include contacting installers, service technicians, equipment distributors, warehouse partners, clients and sales agents to ensure our clients receive superior service and care through the installation/service process. The ideal candidate will be someone who knows how to work collaboratively and respectfully with all parties, has critical thinking skills and a make-it-happen attitude. Theymust also be flexible to work during our hours of operation-Monday to Sunday 8AM to 9PM.\r\n\r\nThe Dispatch Coordinator is responsible to ensure every job is completed in a timely manner, as well as to document and escalate any installation related issues to their manager. This role is a cornerstone in the efficient operation of the Installation team.\r\n\r\nWe are a high-growth company and recognized as one of Canadas Best Places to Work. Our team values a make-it-happen mindset and looks to bring on professionals who desire to grow in a fast-paced environment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Duties/Tasks:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Dispatch, schedule and close out client installation/service calls.</li>\r\n 	<li>Process service requests prepare paperwork for escalated calls to ensure full customer satisfaction using both common and proprietary concepts, practices, and procedures.</li>\r\n 	<li>Schedule and dispatch workers, work crews, equipment, or service vehicles to appropriate locations according to customer requests, specifications, or needs.</li>\r\n 	<li>Arrange for necessary repairs to restore service and schedules.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Relay work orders, messages, and information to or from work crews, supervisors, and field inspectors via telephone.</li>\r\n 	<li>Confer with customers or supervising personnel to address questions, problems, and requests for service or equipment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare daily run schedules.</li>\r\n 	<li>Receive and prepare work orders.</li>\r\n 	<li>Oversee all communications within specifically assigned territories.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Monitor personnel and/or equipment locations and utilization to coordinate service and schedules.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and maintain files and records of customer requests, work or services performed, charges, expenses, inventory, and other dispatch information.</li>\r\n 	<li>Determine types or amounts of equipment, vehicles, materials, or personnel required according to work orders or specifications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Order supplies and equipment and issue them to personnel.</li>\r\n 	<li>Develop a deep understanding of all company products, services and processes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Key Competencies:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Action oriented.</li>\r\n 	<li>Exceptional Communication, both written and verbal in English.</li>\r\n 	<li>Critical thinking and problem-solving skills dealing with individual and unique situations as they arise.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to process high volumes of work with accuracy and attention to detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>Able to work on several tasks at once, with competing priorities.</li>\r\n 	<li>Demonstrate high collaboration within and across teams to get the job done.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Experience Required:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>2+ years of experience in a dispatch role.</li>\r\n 	<li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (Outlook, Excel and Word)</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven experience in exceptional communication and organization.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to learn new processes and systems.</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in dispatch or home services is preferred.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease note this role requires flexibility for shifts Monday through Sunday, 8AM-9PM.\r\n\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Dispatch Coordinator, Installations', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dispatch-coordinator-installations__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-01 16:34:39', '2021-03-01 16:34:39', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1127', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1129, 9, '2021-02-18 16:28:23', '2021-02-18 16:28:23', '<strong><u>Intermediate and Senior Collections Specialist, North York, ON, Full Time.</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Find your spot at Simply Group!</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! https://www.mysimplygroup.com\r\n\r\nAt the Simply Group our employees are the heart of our company. We offer competitive salaries and monthly bonuses to reward hard work and enthusiasm. We offer paid vacation and great extended health benefits. Simply has a flexible work schedule with weekday shifts between 8AM and 8PM, Saturday shifts between 8:30AM and 12:00PM. Further your career with Simply and join one of the fastest growing companies in Canada!\r\n\r\n<strong>Position Summary:</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are looking for experienced Collections Specialists at the intermediate and senior level to provide support to our growing Collections team. Managing past due accounts and providing excellent customer service while collaborating on payment terms with customers are a large part of the Collections Specialists day-to-day work. The ideal candidate will be able to work flexible hours, is motivated, enthusiastic, outgoing and has a passion for helping people.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Serve as team member in the Simply Group Collections team-Crown Crest Capital.</li>\r\n 	<li>Confirm the right party is reached to facilitate credit recovery discussions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Negotiate payment terms and methods. The process often requires reviewing the account information in database, and/or asking probing questions of the customer in order to better understand potential objections to payment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Overcome stalls and objections &amp; suggest solutions for debt payment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Utilize payment options (credit cards, direct checks) and secure this information so that administrative services can process.</li>\r\n 	<li>Negotiate settlements outside of normal guidelines, authorize credit bureaus deletions, negotiate payment arrangements over a longer span of time than normal and close accounts within certain guidelines.</li>\r\n 	<li>May advise management regarding collection strategy effectiveness for various portfolios.</li>\r\n 	<li>May help resolve higher level disputes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Must be able to make 150 calls per day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Experience Required:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Post-Secondary Diploma or Certificate in business administration or related field of study.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Minimum 3 Years of Accounts Receivable\\Collections experience in a call center environment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>3 years of experience in the following areas: Banking and Finance Industry.</li>\r\n 	<li>Minimum of 2 Years of Skip Trace experience required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Skills Required:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Make-it-happen perspective and approach.</li>\r\n 	<li>Must be able to handle stress.</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent customer service skills and the ability to be courteous and persuasive.</li>\r\n 	<li>Exceptional communication, both written and verbal (English).</li>\r\n 	<li>Critical thinking and problem-solving skill set.</li>\r\n 	<li>Goal oriented and able to make business focused decisions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to process high volumes of work with accuracy and attention to detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (Outlook, Excel and Word).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process. </strong>', 'Intermediate and Senior Collections Specialist', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'intermediate-and-senior-collections-specialist', '', '', '2021-02-18 16:28:23', '2021-02-18 16:28:23', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1129', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1130, 9, '2021-02-18 16:29:27', '2021-02-18 16:29:27', '<strong><u>Marketing Manager Job Description</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Full Time, North York, ON</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Your Spot at Simply Group!</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\r\n\r\nWe\'re on the hunt for a talented, skilled, best-in-class marketer to join our growing team. Reporting to the Senior Manager, Digital Marketing, this ambitious self-starter will drive and execute a wide range of marketing campaigns and reporting activities.\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate is comfortable planning and executing traditional marketing campaigns that increase brand awareness, engage and activate audiences, and drive meaningful communications. The position requires a flexible professional that can respond to evolving business priorities and needs in a fast-paced environment. They must have the ability to multi-task and communicate effectively with various audiences, be a strong writer, and possess meticulous attention to detail. Working knowledge of digital marketing is an asset. If you\'re a skilled marketer and a great team player, we\'d like to meet you!\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Duties/Tasks</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Assist in the planning and execution of all marketing activities and promotional programs to drive interest and sales</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure brand messaging is strong and consistent across all channels and marketing efforts (including events, email campaigns, web pages and promotional material)</li>\r\n 	<li>Own the marketing automation process for all brands, including program setup and deployment, nurture paths and communication touchpoints, audience segmentation requirements, database management, etc.</li>\r\n 	<li>Understand key marketing performance metrics to provide forecasts, competitive analysis, campaign results and consumer trends to translate results into actionable insights</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with cross-functional business groups to uncover insights and opportunities to develop and implement marketing strategies to boost brand awareness</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitor the competition (acquisitions, pricing changes and new products and features)</li>\r\n 	<li>Measuring and reporting performance of all marketing campaigns, identifying trends and insights and optimizing spend and performance based on the insights</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with external agencies and vendors to manage ongoing programs and budgets</li>\r\n 	<li>Other duties as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bachelor\'s degree or college equivalent program in marketing, business, communications or a related subject</li>\r\n 	<li>4-5 years\' experience working in a marketing manager rolein a company with multiple lines of business</li>\r\n 	<li>Successful track record in marketing fundamentals and creating marketing campaigns</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent leadership, communication decision-making and organizational skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Demonstrated experience using CRM and marketing automation tools</li>\r\n 	<li>Working knowledge in online analytics tools (Google Analytics, Omniture, WebTrends) is an asset</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience with digital and print marketing, content marketing and social media marketing</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent written (spelling, grammar, punctuation, etc.) and oral communication skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong analytical skills and data-driven thinking</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to meet deadlines and a \"get it done\" no-task-to-small attitude</li>\r\n 	<li>Self-motivated and independent team player who strives for excellence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Marketing Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marketing-manager', '', '', '2021-03-15 18:48:23', '2021-03-15 18:48:23', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1130', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
