(1134, 9, '2021-02-26 17:41:09', '2021-02-26 17:41:09', '<strong><u>Funding Specialist, Full Time, Toronto</u></strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Position Summary: </strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Green Home Services is looking for a Funding Specialist to join our team which operates through our Crown Crest Capital Management division. This role is the operational liaison between our sales department and the finance department, directly impacting revenue generation for the company, and ensuring exceptional service for our customers. The ideal candidate will be able to work independently as well as with the team. They will be able to communicate and meet deadlines set out by established procedures and be accountable to accurately complete their assigned tasks with minimal supervision. Please note this is a Full-time position that operates Monday through Friday 8 am  6 pm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Responsible for auditing completed deals on a weekly basis</li>\r\n 	<li>Completion of Funding process every Friday according to procedures</li>\r\n 	<li>Upload funded deals to eLease to commence billing</li>\r\n 	<li>Process Postponement requests, NOSI registrations and NOSI discharges as required</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage Postponement and Discharges inboxes</li>\r\n 	<li>Assist with financial auditing when requested</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide support where necessary to other teams within the organization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Key Competencies:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Ability to communicate in a professional and approachable manner.</li>\r\n 	<li>Exceptionalcommunication, both written and verbal in English.</li>\r\n 	<li>Detail oriented with the ability to share information effectively across teams</li>\r\n 	<li>Able to work on several tasks at once, with competing priorities.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to process high volumes of work with accuracy and attention to detail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Experience:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completion of post-secondary education in finance, or equivalent.</li>\r\n 	<li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (Outlook, Excel and Word)</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven experience in exceptional communication and organization.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to learn new processes and systems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSimply Green Home Services offers a competitive salary,performancebonusopportunitiesand participation in our group benefits program.\r\n\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process.</strong>', 'Funding Specialist', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'funding-specialist__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-04 18:31:18', '2021-03-04 18:31:18', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1134', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1136, 9, '2021-03-04 18:33:48', '2021-03-04 18:33:48', '<strong><u>Customer Experience Consultant, Full Time, Toronto</u></strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Position Summary:</strong>\r\n\r\nWorking from our call center, the Customer Experience Consultant can anticipate supporting our sales team to complete customer verification calls and move through the required sales approval process, all while maintaining Simply Greens family focused approach and top-notch professionalism. The ideal candidate will be able to work various shifts including evenings and weekends, is motivated, enthusiastic, outgoing and has a passion for helping people.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Complete third-party verification calls to 100% of required compliance.</li>\r\n 	<li>Review and confirm customer credit checks within strict confidentiality measures.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and maintain customer database entries in a timely and accurate fashion.</li>\r\n 	<li>Leverage training and product knowledge to troubleshoot and explain HVAC functions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Address daily questions and inquiries from customers to help solve concerns, or direct them as appropriate to tier two service levels.</li>\r\n 	<li>Record and maintain files and records of customer requests, work or services performed, charges, expenses, inventory, and other dispatch information.</li>\r\n 	<li>Order supplies and equipment, and issue them to service technicians.</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintain the highest level of professionalism and go above and beyond to treat our customers like family.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Key Competencies:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Ability to communicate in a professional and approachable manner.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to take the initiative to resolve customer concerns above the expected solution without compromising business objectives.</li>\r\n 	<li>Critical thinking and problem-solving skills dealing with individual and unique customer needs.</li>\r\n 	<li>Exceptional communication, both written and verbal in English.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ownership of the customer experience journey.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to learn new information and systems quickly with a proven ability to multitask.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to process high volumes of work with accuracy and attention to detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>Passionate to succeed and dedicated to supporting the team.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Experience:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completion of high school diploma or equivalent.</li>\r\n 	<li>At least 1 year of customer service experience.</li>\r\n 	<li>Professional experience in determining customer needs and presenting solutions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (Outlook, Excel and Word)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous experience in a call center an asset.</li>\r\n 	<li>Post-secondary education an asset.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease note this role requires flexibility for shifts Monday through Sunday, 8AM-10PM.\r\n\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process.</strong>', 'Customer Experience Consultant', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'customer-experience-consultant', '', '', '2021-03-15 18:20:05', '2021-03-15 18:20:05', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1136', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1138, 9, '2021-03-09 15:59:02', '2021-03-09 15:59:02', '<strong><u>Sr. Marketing Manager</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>About Us</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities, and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\r\n\r\nWere looking for a highly skilled Sr. Marketing Manager to help us promote our offerings by identifying consumer insights to drive meaningful communications. We need an energetic and intuitive marketer with a deep understanding of creative development. Adept in online and traditional marketing, and highly skilled in visual communications.\r\n\r\nAs the Sr. Marketing Manager, you will manage the graphic design and content development team to deliver engaging content that meets the expectations of our customers. You should be extremely creative, dedicated, and possess excellent written and verbal communication skills. Our ideal candidate will have extensive agency experience working with creatives, and a comprehensive knowledge of branding. He/she will develop plans to help establish our brand, allocating resources to different projects and consulting on short-term and long-term department goals. The successful candidate will have the ability to lead a team of content developers and designers and will drive creativity and enthusiasm in others. If youre a skilled Marketing strategist, able to inspire your team members, wed like to meet you.\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Duties/Tasks</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Work with and manage the creative team to produce new ideas for company branding, promotional campaigns, and marketing communications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and implement tailored marketing plans for the different lines of business.</li>\r\n 	<li>Shape brand standards and create procedures to ensure all creative execution is brand appropriate.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure brand messaging is strong and consistent across all channels and marketing efforts (including events, email campaigns, web pages and promotional material).</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage the project initiation process across all brands and business units and drive the creative execution process.</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage end-to-end marketing deliverables  brief development, creative briefing, creative development, timing, budget.</li>\r\n 	<li>Evaluate trends, assess new data and keep up-to-date with the latest marketing techniques.</li>\r\n 	<li>Supervise the department\'s daily workflow, assign project workload, and monitor deadlines and budgets.</li>\r\n 	<li>Hold regular meetings with program directors to review pipeline, resolve challenges, and present possible solutions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with the cross-functional business teams to uncover insights and opportunities to develop and implement marketing strategies.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set, monitor and report on team goals.</li>\r\n 	<li>Effectively manage a team of 3 by delivering sound creative and executional excellence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bachelors degree in marketing, advertising, or communications</li>\r\n 	<li>Successful track record in marketing roles and creating marketing campaigns</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent leadership, communication, decision-making and organizing skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical and creative thinking</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience with digital and print marketing, content marketing, and social media marketing</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to plan and manage budgets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Simply Group offers a competitive salary, performance bonus opportunities and participation in our group benefits program. All candidates will be considered; however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is happy to provide accommodation through the recruitment and interview process, and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Senior Marketing Manager', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'senior-marketing-manager__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-10 19:37:26', '2021-03-10 19:37:26', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1138', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1140, 2, '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', 'Corporate philanthropy is a key component of our Simply Group valueswe are committed to contributing to the health, growth, and sustainability of our communities and its people. One cause that we especially hold near and dear is supporting the young people in our community.\r\n\r\nIn 2020, Simply Group was extremely proud to partner with <a href=\"https://jack.org/Home\">Jack.org</a>, an initiative that trains and empowers young Canadians to lead the charge in revolutionizing mental across the country. Through various charity training programs, Jack.org brings together young leaders who work to identify strategies and break down barriers to positive mental health in their communities. They also provide resources to enable young people to better understand and educate themselves about their own mental health.\r\n\r\nWith support and contributions from our leadership, employees, and partners, Simply Group was able to raise $22,000 in just 19 days for Jack.org. All of the money was put toward helping 40,000 young people across Canada access vital mental health education and resources.\r\n\r\nThis charitable drive would not have been possible without the entire Simply Group family coming together as a community to support Jack.orgs mission. We can only hope that our contribution made a lasting impact, and we look forward to partnering with Jack.org again!\r\n\r\nTo learn more about Simply Groups charitable initiatives, please visit <a href=\"https://www.mysimplycares.com/\">mysimplycares.com</a>.', 'Simply Group Raises Over $20,000 for Mental Health Initiatives', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'simply-group-raises-over-20000-for-mental-health-initiatives', '', '', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=1140', 0, 'press_release', '', 0),
