ion of our lending portfolio for the last eight years and we see this partnership as a tremendous opportunity for both organizations to execute on their growth strategies.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1065,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-style\":\"button\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200908005292/en/VersaBank-Adds-Simply-Group-Financial-Point-of-Sale-Partner\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:block-lab/half-and-half {\"title\":\"Simply Green Home Services To Make Friendly, Premium All-Cash Offer to Acquire Dealnet\",\"copy\":\"\\u003cp\\u003e\\u0022Simply Green has invested strategically to become a leader in the home comfort and home energy solutions sector, and this deal represents the next step in our continued growth. We are pleased this transaction will be adding over $200 million of finance receivables to our growing business, said Lawrence Krimker, Chief Executive Officer of Simply Group. With Simply Greens expansive and growing product offerings, and Dealnets underlying strength, we believe this acquisition will benefit our customers and investors and positions us well for the future. We look forward to commencing the tender process as soon as possible.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"image\":1051,\"background-styles\":\"background-repeat: no-repeat;\\nbackground-position: center center;\\nbackground-size: cover;\\nmargin-bottom:40px;\",\"link-list\":{\"rows\":[{\"\":\"\",\"link-url\":\"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2020/10/27/2114761/0/en/Simply-Group-Acquisition-Corp-Acquires-93-13-of-Dealnet-Capital-Corp-and-Commences-Compulsory-Acquisition.html\",\"link-text\":\"Read More\",\"link-style\":\"button\"}]}} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Investors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '156-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-03-10 15:57:31', '2021-03-10 15:57:31', '', 156, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/156-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1153, 9, '2021-03-10 19:38:29', '2021-03-10 19:38:29', '<strong><u>Senior Marketing Manager</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>About Us</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities, and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\r\n\r\nWere looking for a highly skilled Sr. Marketing Manager to help us promote our offerings by identifying consumer insights to drive meaningful communications. We need an energetic and intuitive marketer with a deep understanding of creative development. Adept in online and traditional marketing, and highly skilled in visual communications.\r\n\r\nAs the Sr. Marketing Manager, you will manage the graphic design and content development team to deliver engaging content that meets the expectations of our customers. You should be extremely creative, dedicated, and possess excellent written and verbal communication skills. Our ideal candidate will have extensive agency experience working with creatives, and a comprehensive knowledge of branding. He/she will develop plans to help establish our brand, allocating resources to different projects and consulting on short-term and long-term department goals. The successful candidate will have the ability to lead a team of content developers and designers and will drive creativity and enthusiasm in others. If youre a skilled Marketing strategist, able to inspire your team members, wed like to meet you.\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Duties/Tasks</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Work with and manage the creative team to produce new ideas for company branding, promotional campaigns, and marketing communications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and implement tailored marketing plans for the different lines of business.</li>\r\n 	<li>Shape brand standards and create procedures to ensure all creative execution is brand appropriate.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure brand messaging is strong and consistent across all channels and marketing efforts (including events, email campaigns, web pages and promotional material).</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage the project initiation process across all brands and business units and drive the creative execution process.</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage end-to-end marketing deliverables  brief development, creative briefing, creative development, timing, budget.</li>\r\n 	<li>Evaluate trends, assess new data and keep up-to-date with the latest marketing techniques.</li>\r\n 	<li>Supervise the department\'s daily workflow, assign project workload, and monitor deadlines and budgets.</li>\r\n 	<li>Hold regular meetings with program directors to review pipeline, resolve challenges, and present possible solutions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with the cross-functional business teams to uncover insights and opportunities to develop and implement marketing strategies.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set, monitor and report on team goals.</li>\r\n 	<li>Effectively manage a team of 3 by delivering sound creative and executional excellence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bachelors degree in marketing, advertising, or communications</li>\r\n 	<li>5-8 years professional experience working in marketing, communications, campaign management, marketing strategy, creative development or similar experience</li>\r\n 	<li>Successful track record in marketing roles and creating marketing campaigns</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent leadership, communication, decision-making, organizing, analytical and creative thinking skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience with digital and print marketing, content marketing, and social media marketing</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience managing a minimum of 1-2 direct reports</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to plan and manage budgets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All candidates will be considered, however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Simply Group is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the hiring process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Our HR Team will work with applicants requesting accommodations at any stage of the hiring process.</strong>', 'Senior Marketing Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'senior-marketing-manager', '', '', '2021-03-10 21:34:29', '2021-03-10 21:34:29', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1153', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
